						<summary>

						<p>Stone standing in the field called Khānāpuradavara-hola.</p>						

						<p>1580 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription is dated Śaka [150]2, [Vi]krama, Vaiśākha śu. 11 corresponding to A.D. 1580, April 25. It seems to record a <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> gift of land to a person (name not clear) of the Gautama-gōtra and Ṛik-śākhā.</p>						

						</summary>
